						               													<description>Players talk as fast as they can in 20 seconds to guess the 10 hidden clue words that are all related to the &amp;ldquo;Subject&amp;rdquo; word displayed at the top of the card displayed on the game board.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first team&amp;rsquo;s number of unguessed words determines how many clues the second Team will get to see in their attempt to guess a new &amp;ldquo;Subject&amp;rdquo; word.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;For example: Team A guesses 7 out the 10 words under the subject of &amp;ldquo;Pizza.&amp;rdquo; The total score for this round will eventually be 7 points, but we don&amp;rsquo;t yet know which Team has won those points&amp;hellip;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In our example, Team B is allowed only three clue words (10-7) on a new card to guess what the &amp;ldquo;Subject&amp;rdquo; of that card is. If Team B correctly guesses the new Subject from those clues, they win the points for the round (7, in this case). If Team B fails to identify the subject, Team A wins those points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game continues with Teams switching roles--Team B will try to guess the 10 hidden clue words on a new card. Team A will follow with using a limited number of words to guess a new Subject.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Talk About is a faithful adaptation of an Canadian television game show, whose gameplay seems to have been inspired by the board game Outburst!.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
